history.content:
Hello, if the class is 70% full, that is likely why you're on the wait list. Have you reviewed this? https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/cs/degree-reqs/enrollment-policy

  1. Each upper div class in which getting sufficient TA support is not identified as uncertain will be set up to allow initial enrollment up to 70% of projected enrollment capacity.

I know under the new enrollment system that it's forcing everyone to waitlist if someone is already on the waitlist, and then eligible students are taken off. However I've been waitlisted for a while now since my phase 1 which was almost 2 weeks ago, and I'm wondering if it's normal to still be waitlisted. (I'm declared L&S CS with senior standing). I'm slightly concerned cause the class is already 70% full.
history.subject: CS 160 Enrollment
